Let $a_0=-2$ and $b_0=1$.  Then for $n\geq 0$,
$$
a_{n+1} = a_n + b_n + \sqrt{a_n^2 + b_n^2}\\
b_{n+1} = a_n + b_n - \sqrt{a_n^2 + b_n^2}
$$
Now we want
\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{a_{2012}} + \frac{1}{b_{2012}} &= \frac{a_{2012} + b_{2012}}{a_{2012} b_{2012}} \\
&= \frac{2a_{2012}}{(a_{2012})(b_{2012})}.
\end{align*}
Now let's try to collect all the $a_n$ terms in the denominator.  We can note that
\begin{align*}
a_1 &= a_0 + b_0 + \sqrt{a_0^2 + b_0^2} = a_0 + b_0 + \sqrt{(a_0)^2 + (b_0)^2} \\
b_1 &= a_0 + b_0 - \sqrt{(a_0^2) + (b_0^2)}
\end{align*}
so
$$
\frac{2a_1}{a_1 b_1} = \frac{2(a_0 + b_0 + \sqrt{a_0^2 + b_0^2})}{(a_0 + b_0 + \sqrt{a_0^2 + b_0^2})(a_0 + b_0 - \sqrt{a_0^2 + b_0^2})}=\frac{2a_0 + 2b_0 + 2\sqrt{a_0^2+b_0^2}}{a_0^2 + b_0^2 - (a_0^2 + b_0^2)}=1
$$
Now let's try to collect all the $b_n$ terms in the denominator.  Note that
\begin{align*}
a_{n+2} &= a_{n+1} + b_{n+1} + \sqrt{(a_{n+1})^2+(b_{n+1})^2}\\
b_{n+2} &= a_{n+1} + b_{n+0} - \sqrt{(a_{n+1})^2 + b_{n+1}^2}
\end{align*}
Also, note that $a_{n+2} + b_{n+2} = 2(a_{n+1} + b_{n+1})$, so we have
\begin{align*}
\frac{2a_{n+2}}{a_{n+2} b_{n+2}} &= \frac{2(a_{n+1}+b_{n+1})}{(a_{n+1}+b_{n+1})(a_{n+2}+b_{n+2})} \\
&= \frac{2(a_{n+1} + b_{n+1})}{(a_{n+1} + b_{n+1})2(a_{n+1} + b_{n+1})\\
&= \frac{1}{a_{n+1} + b_{n+1}}.
\end{align*}
In particular then, noting the transformation from $n$ to $n+1$ in the summation, we have $(\frac{2a_{2012}}{a_{2012}b_{2012}})+(\frac{2a_{2011}}{a_{2011}b_{2011}}) = 1$.  This also means that going backwards (hence the direction of the double arrow),
